result.execSummary:
The defendant Jade M. Vonbehren was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Parties have reached joint resolution on both matters. Resolution stated by DA. Plea questionnaire/waiver of rights presented. Colloquy. NC pleas entered to 3 counts. Further colloquy. Finding of guilty. Comment on sentencing. 

Sentencing: 15CM148: Ct 1: withhold sentence for 2 yrs probation. Conditions: Engage in, pay for and successfully complete all educational programs and treatment required by agent, pay costs of action and costs of probation, DNA sample and surcharge. No contact with Jamie Hampton without agent approval. Cts 2 & 3 are dismissed and read in.  Probation agent is directed to assist def with getting grief counseling.

15CM151: Ct 1 & 2: withhold sentence for 2 yrs probation. Conditions: Engage in, pay for and successfully complete all assessments and treatment required by agent, pay costs of action and costs of probation, No contact with Jamie Hampton without agent approval. Concurrent to 15CM148. Def is eligible for expungement under 973.015. Def is to contact the clerk's office to follow up with that. Probation agent is directed to assist def with getting grief counseling.
Matter called. Def appears in person. Atty Ritter via telephone. Will reset to tag along with her other matter tomorrow.  Initial appearance scheduled for September 16, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
